column2: One adult loon and two babies. 2nd adult arrived later. Surface of the water is completely smooth.
2 baby loons and 1 adult at separate ends of the lake. Rained about an hour before collecting this reading.
2 baby loons. No adult. Water open at deep hole. Mucky- foliage floating at other end.
2 young loons- one adult. Green heron. Foliage bloom all blown to opposite end of the lake.
lake extremely clear.. 2 almost adult loons diving very close to our kayaks. No parents. Calm surface.
The water is as clear as I ever remember it being. 2 young loons- no adult. Saw flight practice earlier.
Very clear and breezy. No loons - godspeed on your arduous journey! Four largish ducks of unknown species- 5 turtles- 1 dragongly- few small birds and one white butterfly.
Very clear. Little yuck on surface. Saw big trout by the rock. 1 turtle half buried in mud- maybe 10 feet. adequate flow out discharge.
